column5: Only thing open in that stretch is the Lift Locks in Peterborough and lock 20 that will let you into Little Lake.
Luckily I don't use the locks!  lol.  Wayne, any idea on the reason for closure?  Weather related?

With the exception of Rice Lake, most of the waterways from Lakefield south to Trenton get quite narrow and with the huge volume of water flowing south the levels are high and the currents very strong in places.  Lots more rain expected today so I don't spose that's gonna help much either.
I think Lew did something     LOL...It high water levels
